From: Hermes Agent <hermes@nousresearch.com>
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 23:00:00 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 1/4] oplus_charger: Fix fastchg_to_normal deadlock causing charge to
 never resume

When fastchg_to_normal() or fastchg_to_warm() returns true, the charger
state machine blocks charging. After the temperature/soc condition clears
and these flags return false, the charger should resume — but the static
'charger_resumed' variable stays 'true' and the else-if condition
`charger_resumed == false` never evaluates true again, permanently
locking out charging.

Fix by:
1. Removing the `charger_resumed == false` condition from the resume
   path — charger_resumed should only gate the first attempt after boot.
2. Setting `charger_resumed = false` inside the fastchg_to_normal/warm
   block so the driver attempts to resume once the condition clears.

Thermal protection is NOT removed — charging still stops when hot.
It just properly resumes when the device cools down.

Signed-off-by: Hermes Agent <hermes@nousresearch.com>
---
 drivers/power/oppo/oplus_charger.c | 9 +++++----
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/power/oppo/oplus_charger.c b/drivers/power/oppo/oplus_charger.c
index 9c80b1e2a..f37d9b1c0 100644
--- a/drivers/power/oppo/oplus_charger.c
+++ b/drivers/power/oppo/oplus_charger.c
@@ -5285,15 +5285,16 @@ void oplus_charger_detect_check(struct oplus_chg_chip *chip)
 		} else {
 			if (oplus_vooc_get_fastchg_to_normal() == true
 					|| oplus_vooc_get_fastchg_to_warm() == true) {
-				/*do nothing*/
+				/* transition in progress — reset so we retry once it clears */
+				charger_resumed = false;
 				charger_xlog_printk(CHG_LOG_CRTI,
 					"fast_to_normal or to_warm 2,don't turn on charge here\n");
 				if (oplus_vooc_get_reset_adapter_st()) {
 					oplus_chg_unsuspend_charger();
 				}
-			} else if (oplus_vooc_get_fastchg_started() == false
-					&& charger_resumed == false) {
-				charger_resumed = chip->chg_ops->check_charger_resume();
+			} else if (oplus_vooc_get_fastchg_started() == false) {
+				if (!charger_resumed)
+					charger_resumed = chip->chg_ops->check_charger_resume();
 				oplus_chg_turn_on_charging(chip);
 
 			}
